h1. Ruby Method Exercises


h2. 1. Simple greeting

Create a method which greets you when given a name. The method should return a string

It should function as follows:

name = "Bob"
greet name # => "Hello Bob!"


h2. 2. Repeat exercise 1, but instead of return a string use the 'puts' command to output the greeting 5 times

h2. 3. Create a 'multiply' method to multiply any two given numbers.

For example:

sum(4, 6) # => 10

h2. 4. Repeat exercise 1, but this time specify a default value for the name.
